presented_choices:
["Hi Students. look out for the number of swaps in a sequence. If you swap in a rightly arranged sequence of 5 8 times, that's very out of order.","Start by comparing the first two blocks. Then progress by comparing the blocks in the 2nd and 3rd position, and then the 3rd and 4th, and so on.

Whenever a swap happens, keep note of the \"leading\" block that was placed ahead (to the right). If a swap does not happen, the block on the right that was compared becomes the new \"leading\" block. The block that was just swapped behind the \"leading\" block then needs to be compared to the block behind it. If a swap happens, again compare it to the block behind it.
